nt and having found such a tremendous partner in clayton venture group said don sharp ceo of coolfire solutions bringing together the respective strengths of our two organizations will further align the organizations and position us for even greater growth over the long term while we have already achieved tremendous success together we believe this investment will take our strategic relationship to the next level coolfire solutions will use proceeds from the investment to accelerate its growth as well as the evolution of its ronin mobile software platform which enterprise holdings currently licenses coolfire solutions leverages data from the internet of things iot and a variety of other sources to improve situational awareness for leadingedge businesses coolfire solutions also uses its flexible mobile platform to connect people assets and information in a way that leads to quick decisionmaking and action this investment further cements coolfire solutions relationship with cvg and enterprise holdings cvg was established in  to strategically invest in emerging technology companies with a focus on mobility fleet connectivity and management and autonomous technology for more information about clayton venture group contact cvgehicom  about coolfire solutions inccoolfire solutions inc was formed in  to bring mobile technology to the us military special operators coolfire solutions continues to work with tier  special operations units across the world and is now bringing its experience and our technology to the commercial marketplace coolfire solutions connects people assets and information across any platform leveraging data from any source across any device environment or network in realtime to enable better decision making at the edge contactben langlinaiscoolfire solutionsblanglinaiscoolfiresolutionscom     to view the original version on pr newswire visithttpwwwprnewswirecomnewsreleasescoolfiresolutionsreceivesinvestmentfromclaytonventuregrouphtml source coolfire solu